<subSubSection id="C359FCF8FFC9FFE8FF549DE3FD0D069C" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFCAF73FFC9FFE8FF549DE3FB4206F0" blockId="3.[136,1451,911,1262]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FF549DE3FF2801DB" bold="true" box="[136,210,912,938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFC9FFE8FF079DE3FE5C01D8" box="[219,422,911,938]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindleyana">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FF079DE3FE5C01D8" box="[219,422,911,938]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Cassia lindleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on the collection 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FCBB9DFCFC0301D8" box="[871,1017,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Gardner 367</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F354EFE3FFC9FFE8FB9D9DFCFB7201D8" box="[1089,1160,911,937]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but the only information contained in the original description for typification purposes is plants from the “Organ Mountains, hab. in woods, common”. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFC9FFE8FEDE9DA4FE170183" author="Bentham, G." box="[258,493,983,1010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" pagination="1 - 528" refId="ref4953" refString="Bentham, G. (1870) Leguminosae II. Et III. Swartzieae, Caesalpinieae, Mimoseae. In: Martius, K. F. P. von, Eichler, A. W. &amp; Urban, I. (Eds.) Flora Brasiliensis. vol. XV, Pars II, Fasc. 50. Lipsiae, Londinensis., pp. 1 - 528." type="book chapter" year="1870">Bentham (1870: 123)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFC9FFE8FDAC9DABFCFE0180" box="[624,772,983,1010]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindleyana">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FDAC9DABFCFE0180" box="[624,772,983,1010]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">C. lindleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFC9FFE8FC559DABFBE80180" box="[905,1042,983,1010]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multijuga">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FC559DABFBE80180" box="[905,1042,983,1010]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">C. multijuga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the collection 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FACA9DA4FA5E0180" box="[1302,1444,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Gardner 367</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFC9FFE8FF549D88FE370667" author="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C." box="[136,461,1019,1046]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" pagination="1 - 454" refId="ref5268" refString="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C. (1982) The American Cassiinae: A synoptical revision of Leguminosae tribe Cassieae subtribe Cassiinae in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 35: 1 - 454." type="journal article" year="1982">Irwin &amp; Barneby (1982: 498)</bibRefCitation>
changed the status of 
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFC9FFE8FD1D9D8FFC020664" authorityName="H. S. Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Gardner" box="[705,1016,1019,1046]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="multijuga" variety="lindleyana">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FD1D9D8FFCB10664" box="[705,843,1019,1046]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">C. multijuga</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FC5E9D88FC020664" box="[898,1016,1019,1045]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">lindleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the subspecies level, and mistakenly indicated the specimen of the collection 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FD8B9A6CFD130648" box="[599,745,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Gardner 367</emphasis>
as the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFC9FFE8FCE09A6CFC5B0648" box="[828,929,1055,1081]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">holotype</typeStatus>
, under barcode K000555411, deposited at the Kew Herbarium (K). The species protologue, however, does not indicate where the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFC9FFE8FBEC9A30FB68062C" box="[1072,1170,1091,1117]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">holotype</typeStatus>
was deposited, and there is no indication that the specimen suggested by those authors was the material used by Gardner.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFCAF73FFC9FFE8FF619AFFFD0D069C" blockId="3.[136,1451,911,1262]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">
We found 
<specimenCount id="9D4564FAFFC9FFE8FEF29AF8FE2306D4" box="[302,473,1163,1189]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" type="generic">nine specimens</specimenCount>
from the collection 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC9FFE8FD699AF8FCBE06D4" box="[693,836,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">
<location id="8E9CF9A8FFC9FFE8FD699AF8FCEE06D4" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03EA1E65FFC9FFE8FF549C1CFD0D069C:8E9CF9A8FFC9FFE8FD699AF8FCEE06D4" box="[693,788,1163,1189]" country="Brazil" name="Gardner" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Gardner</location>
367
</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F354EFE3FFC9FFE8FC5A9AF8FC3706D4" box="[902,973,1163,1189]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and designate here the specimen deposited at K, under barcode K000555411 as the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFC9FFE8FD919ADCFD4E06B8" box="[589,692,1199,1225]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189">lectotype</typeStatus>
as it is well preserved, and also because (according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFC9FFE8FAC79ADCFA5906BB" author="Thiers, B." box="[1307,1443,1199,1226]" pageId="3" pageNumber="189" refId="ref6117" refString="Thiers, B. (2021) Index Herbariorum: a global directory of public herbaria and associated staff. New York Botanical Garden's Virtual Herbarium, New York. Available from: http: // sweetgum. nybg. org / ih / (accessed 25 July 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Thiers 2021</bibRefCitation>
) the Kew Herbarium houses Gardner’s main collections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
